#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.23:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Anuttariyavagga "
msgstr "3. Unsurpassable "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Bhayasutta "
msgstr "23. Dangers "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.311, sc1
msgctxt "an6.23:1.1"
msgid "“‘Bhayan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ; "
msgstr "“‘Danger’, mendicants, is a term for sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "an6.23:1.2"
msgid "‘dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Suffering’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:1.3"
msgid "‘rogo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ; "
msgstr "‘disease’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:1.4"
msgid "‘gaṇḍo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ; "
msgstr "‘boil’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:1.5"
msgid "‘saṅgo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ; "
msgstr "‘tie’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:1.6"
msgid "‘paṅko’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "and ‘bog’ are terms for sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.23:2.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, ‘bhayan’ti kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ? "
msgstr "And why is ‘danger’ a term for sensual pleasures? "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.2"
msgid "Kāmarāgarattāyaṃ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi bhayā na parimuccati, samparāyikāpi bhayā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘bhayan’ti kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "Someone who is caught up in sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is not freed from dangers in the present life or in lives to come. That is why ‘danger’ is a term for sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.23:2.3"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhanti … pe … "
msgstr "And why are ‘suffering’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.4"
msgid "rogoti … "
msgstr "‘disease’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.5"
msgid "gaṇḍoti … "
msgstr "‘boil’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.6"
msgid "saṅgoti … "
msgstr "‘tie’, "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.7"
msgid "paṅkoti kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ? "
msgstr "and ‘bog’ terms for sensual pleasures? "

msgctxt "an6.23:2.8"
msgid "Kāmarāgarattāyaṃ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi paṅkā na parimuccati, samparāyikāpi paṅkā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘paṅko’ti kāmānametaṃ adhivacananti. "
msgstr "Someone who is caught up in sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is not freed from suffering, disease, boils, ties, or bogs in the present life or in lives to come. That is why these are terms for sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an6.23:3.1"
msgid "Bhayaṃ dukkhaṃ rogo gaṇḍo, "
msgstr "Danger, suffering, disease, boils, "

# NOTE: here I follow the Comm. But I suspect that ubhaya refers to “on both sides” (i.e. here and beyond).
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.2"
msgid "saṅgo paṅko ca ubhayaṃ; "
msgstr "and ties and bogs both. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.3"
msgid "Ete kāmā pavuccanti, "
msgstr "These describe the sensual pleasures "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.4"
msgid "yattha satto puthujjano. "
msgstr "to which ordinary people are attached. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an6.23:4.1"
msgid "Upādāne bhayaṃ disvā, "
msgstr "Seeing the danger in grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.2"
msgid "jātimaraṇasambhave; "
msgstr "the origin of birth and death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.3"
msgid "Anupādā vimuccanti, "
msgstr "they’re freed by not grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.4"
msgid "jātimaraṇasaṅkhaye. "
msgstr "with the ending of birth and death. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an6.23:5.1"
msgid "Te khemappattā sukhino, "
msgstr "Happy, they’ve come to a safe place, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:5.2"
msgid "diṭṭhadhammābhinibbutā; "
msgstr "extinguished in this very life. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Sabbaverabhayātītā → sabbe verabhayātītā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.23:5.3"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātītā, "
msgstr "They’ve gone beyond all threats and dangers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:5.4"
msgid "sabbadukkhaṃ upaccagun”ti. "
msgstr "and risen above all suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.23:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
